<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98581328632626></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98581328632626><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98581328632626>RE: Erudite SK General Questions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=98581328632626#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Mar 28th 4:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.15]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, you can regain Ven Sathir faction in a couple of ways, and it does not require killing level 60 mobs =)<br><br>1)The Sarnak Berserker whip quest in the outpost.&nbsp;&nbsp;Turning 4 in at a time will give you a positive hit and some decent xp depending on your level.  This can be tedious, but is a fairly easy way to fix faction as every berserker will have a whip.  This won't help much if you already have hosed your faction without some trickery (sneak, invis questing, etc).<br><br>2)Hunt in Howling Stones.  My guild leader and a couple others in the guild have hunted so much in there, that they are &gt;warmly&lt; in the outpost.  And for the record, my guild leader is a Dwarf Cleric, and one of the others is a High Elf Paladin.  Both were KOS, but now they freely roam the outpost =)<br><br>Hunting in Karnor's can be a pain if you would like to keep the ability to bank and buy in the outpost.  Basically you have to build up some faction, proceed to lose some, then rebuild.  Is it worth it?  Depends on who you ask.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>Chugrahk<br>30 SK BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
